{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "sweep", "icon": "SOP/sweep", "tags": "model, curveup, splines, curves, core", "version": "", "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sweep"], "extent": [107, 117]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a surface by sweeping cross-sections along a backbone\ncurve."], "extent": [117, 194]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Sweep op sweeps primitives in the Cross-section input along Backbone\ncurve(s), creating ribbon and tube-like shapes. The cross-section\nprimitives are placed at each point of the backbone perpendicular to it.\nIf a Reference Point input is given, each primitive will be oriented to\naim at its corresponding reference point."], "extent": [194, 521]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The backbone curve can be open or closed, but must have at least two\n  points."], "extent": [521, 603]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the backbone input has more than one primitive, Sweep will sweep\n  the cross section along each one."], "extent": [603, 710]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the cross-section input has multiple primitives, you can control\n  them using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cycle type"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [710, 824]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sweep places the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["origin"]}, " of the cross-section on the backbone by\n  default. You can specify a point on the cross-section to attach to the\n  backbone instead with the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Use vertex"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Connection vertex"]}, "\n  parameters."], "extent": [824, 1049]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["In most cases, you should build the cross section primitives in the XY\n  plane. Sweep will automatically orient them properly along the\n  backbone."], "extent": [1049, 1200]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the backbone curve(s) have point colors or texture coordinates,\n  they will be maintained and applied to the cross section primitives."], "extent": [1200, 1341]}], "container": true}, {"type": "include_group", "body": [{"ext": "/shelf/sweep#includeme", "type": "include", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1341, 1375]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1375, 1387], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["X-Section Group"], "extent": [1387, 1408], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Only use the geometry in this group as the cross-section, instead of all geometry in the first input."], "extent": [1434, 1544]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/xgrp"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Path Group"], "extent": [1544, 1560], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Only use the geometry in this group as the backbone curve(s), instead of all geometry in the second input."], "extent": [1589, 1704]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/pathgrp"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Reference Group"], "extent": [1704, 1725], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Only use the geometry in this group as reference points, instead of all geometry in the third input."], "extent": [1753, 1862]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/refgrp"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Cycle Type"], "extent": [1862, 1878], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["How to sweep the primitives."], "extent": [1905, 1942]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/cycle"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Angle Fix"], "extent": [1942, 1957], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Attempt to fix buckling twists."], "extent": [1984, 2024]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/angle"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Fix Flipping"], "extent": [2024, 2042], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Fixes flipped normals."], "extent": [2070, 2101]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/noflip"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Remove Coincident Points on Path"], "extent": [2101, 2139], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Removes overlapping points."], "extent": [2169, 2205]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/skipcoin"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Aim at Reference Points"], "extent": [2205, 2234], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Tilt the cross-sections towards their respective reference points from the Reference Points input.  The Reference Points input will still be used to roll the cross-sections around the backbone even when this parameter is turned off."], "extent": [2264, 2505]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/aimatref"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Vertex"], "extent": [2505, 2521], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Connect a specific vertex of the cross-section to the backbone."], "extent": [2549, 2621]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/usevtx"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Connection Vertex"], "extent": [2621, 2644], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Specific vertex to connect to backbone."], "extent": [2672, 2720]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/vertex"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Transform Using Attributes"], "extent": [2720, 2752], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["When enabled, instead of using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scale"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Twist"]}, ", and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Roll"]}, " parameters,\n        the cross-sections are transformed using the backbone attributes: ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pscale"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["scale"]}, ",\n        ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["trans"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["rot"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["orient"]}, ", and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pivot"]}, ".  If none of ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["trans"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["rot"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["orient"]}, ", or ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pivot"]}, " are specified, (possibly ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pscale"]}, " or ", {"type": "code", "text": ["scale"]}, " still), the rotation from the curve will be used."], "extent": [2780, 3176]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "xformbyattrib"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Scale"], "extent": [3176, 3187], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Uniform scale of cross-section."], "extent": [3214, 3254]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/scale"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Twist"], "extent": [3254, 3265], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Cumulative rotation of cross-sections around the backbone."], "extent": [3292, 3359]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/twist"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Roll"], "extent": [3359, 3369], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Non-cumulative rotation of cross-sections around the backbone."], "extent": [3395, 3466]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/roll"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Create Groups"], "extent": [3466, 3485], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Creates a group for each backbone."], "extent": [3511, 3554]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/newg"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sweep Groups"], "extent": [3554, 3572], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Allows naming of the sweep groups. A separate group is created for each backbone by appending a number to the group name. If there is only one backbone, the created group will be called sweepGroup1."], "extent": [3602, 3809]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/sweepgrp"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Attributes from Path"], "extent": [3809, 3835], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["These point attributes and groups will be copied from the backbone points to the cross-section points.\n        If a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, " attribute is present on both the cross-section and backbone, and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cycle Type"]}, " is set to either ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["One Primitive at a Time"]}, " or ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cycle Primitives"]}, ",\n        only the u component will be copied from the backbone, so the v component will still be from the cross-section ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, " attribute.\n        Although only point attributes are copied from the backbone, there is a special case for if the cross-section has a vertex ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, " attribute, point ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, " values can be\n        copied into the destination vertex ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, " attribute, but this only works for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, "."], "extent": [3859, 4534]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "ptattribs"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Skin Output"], "extent": [4534, 4551], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["How/whether to create a surface connecting the cross-sections along the backbone."], "extent": [4577, 4669]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["Off"], "extent": [4669, 4682], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Do not create a surface."], "extent": [4682, 4719]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["On"], "extent": [4719, 4731], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Skin each set of swept cross-sections."], "extent": [4731, 4782]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["On with Auto Close"], "extent": [4782, 4810], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Skin each set and close if the underlying path is closed."], "extent": [4810, 4880]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["On with Preserve Shape"], "extent": [4880, 4912], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Like ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["On"]}, " above, but ensure the swept curves are fully encased in the resulting surface."], "extent": [4912, 5015]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["On with Preserve Shape and Auto Close"], "extent": [5015, 5062], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Skin with ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Preserve Shape"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Auto Close"]}, " put together."], "extent": [5062, 5136]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/skin"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Fast Sweep"], "extent": [5136, 5152], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["More efficient skinning. Use when the input geometries maintain\n        the same topologies between cooks and each cross-section has the\n        same number of points."], "extent": [5178, 5354]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/fast"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Output Polygons"], "extent": [5354, 5375], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Outputs meshes as polygons rather than meshes."], "extent": [5403, 5458]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/polyout"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [5458, 5466], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Cross-section"], "extent": [5466, 5485], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The geometry to sweep along the backbone curve."], "extent": [5485, 5541]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Backbone path"], "extent": [5541, 5560], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The curve(s) to sweep the cross-section shape along."], "extent": [5560, 5621]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Reference Points"], "extent": [5621, 5643], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["If this input is connected, each primitive will be oriented to\n        aim at its corresponding reference point in this geometry."], "extent": [5643, 5781]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "locals", "container": true, "type": "locals_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [5781, 5789], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["PT"], "extent": [5789, 5797], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Current vertex. It is the current point along the current path."], "extent": [5797, 5869]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["NPT"], "extent": [5869, 5878], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Total number of points."], "extent": [5878, 5910]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["PATH"], "extent": [5910, 5920], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Path primitive number. It tells you which path you are on."], "extent": [5920, 5987]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["PCT"], "extent": [5987, 5996], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Percentage along backbone (path)."], "extent": [5996, 6047]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Locals"}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [6047, 6053], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["$PT"]}, " can\u2019t be used to directly index a point in the source, you need to use ", {"type": "code", "text": ["$PATH"]}, " to access the proper primitive, and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["$PT"]}, " the correct vertex in that primitive. "], "extent": [6053, 6228]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [6228, 6237], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/rails", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rails"}], "extent": [6237, 6260]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/skin", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skin"}], "extent": [6260, 6283]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Sweep"], "summary": ["Creates a surface by sweeping cross-sections along a backbone\ncurve."]}